column9: and two playgrounds. Casey Elementary School has been thoroughly modernized over the past\rseveral decades. The most recent upgrades to the campus occurred in 2002 and included parking lot expansion and construction of a new before- and\rafter-school pick-up area for students. The chart displays the results of the most recent school facilities inspection as of August 2018. Any deficiencies\rlisted in the chart are added to the work order process when time and funding is available\r\rSchool Safety\r\rThe safety of students and staff is a primary concern of Casey Elementary School. All visitors to the campus must sign in at the office and wear a visitor’s\rpass at all times. Supervision is provided to ensure the safety of each student before school
column12: and after school. Supervision is a\rresponsibility shared among parent/guardian volunteers
column14: and administrators. To further safeguard the well-being of students and staff
column15: a\rcomprehensive School Site Safety Plan has been developed by the School Site Council. The Safety Plan was most recently updated in March 2018; any\rrevisions and updates are reviewed immediately with the staff. Key elements of the Safety Plan focus on the following:\r•School rules & procedures\r•Disaster procedures/routine & emergency drills\r•Current status of school crime\r•Notification to teachers\r•Child abuse reporting procedures\r•School-wide dress code\r•Policies related to suspension/expulsion\r•Sexual harassment policy\r•Safe ingress & egress of pupils

column26: and functional learning environment.\r\rMaintenance & Repair\r\rA scheduled maintenance program is administered by the school’s custodial staff on a regular basis
